<leg:level id="UCPN.UCPR.UCPRN05.PT42.D4"><leg:level-vrnt leveltype="division" searchtype="LEGISLATION DIVISION" subdoc="false" toc-caption="DIVISION 4 OFFERS TO CONTRIBUTE [r 42.18]">
<leg:heading><desig searchtype="DIV-NUM"><designum><refpt id="UCPN.UCPR.UCPRN05.PT42.D4" type="ext"/>DIVISION 4</designum></desig><title searchtype="DIV-TITLE">OFFERS TO CONTRIBUTE [r 42.18]</title></leg:heading>
<leg:levelbody>
<leg:level id="UCPN.UCPR.UCPRN05.R42-18"><leg:level-vrnt leveltype="rul" searchtype="LEGISLATION RUL" subdoc="true" toc-caption="[r 42.18] r 42.18 Offer to contribute (cf SCR Part 52A, rule 24; DCR Part 39A, rule 26; LCR Part 31A, rule 21) ">
<leg:levelinfo>
<leg:levelstatus isrepealed="false" ln.user-displayed="false"/></leg:levelinfo>
<leg:heading inline="true"><edpnum><refpt id="UCPN.UCPR.UCPRN05.R42-18" type="ext"/>[r 42.18]</edpnum><title searchtype="RUL-TITLE">Offer to contribute (cf SCR Part 52A, rule 24; DCR Part 39A, rule 26; LCR Part 31A, rule 21) </title><desig searchtype="RUL-NUM"><designum>42.18</designum></desig></leg:heading>
<leg:levelbody>
<leg:bodytext>
<p><text>If a party has made an offer to contribute, as referred to in rule 20.32, the court must take into account both the fact and the amount of the offer in exercising its discretion as to costs.</text></p>
<leg:comntry subdoc="true" toc-caption="NOTES"><heading searchtype="COMMENTARY"><title><refpt id="UCPN.UCPR.UCPRN05.PT42.R18.COM1" type="ext"/>NOTES</title></heading>
<level id="UCPN_UCPR.SGM_UCPN.UCPR.42-18-5" leveltype="para0" subdoc="true" toc-caption="[42.18.5] Costs between contributing parties"><heading searchtype="COMMENTARY"><edpnum><refpt id="UCPN.UCPR.42-18-5" type="ext"/>[42.18.5] </edpnum><title>Costs between contributing parties</title></heading>
<bodytext searchtype="COMMENTARY">
<p>
<text>The rule requires the court take account of any contribution offers made between the parties, but without stipulating the particular consequences that will apply where the offeree&#x2019;s judgment liability is no better than the offer. The absence of any particular prescriptive consequence recognises the range of different issues that can arise in proceedings where multiple parties face potential liability in relation to essentially the same loss. In some instances, for example where liability to the plaintiff is contested, or where the offer only relates to the proportionate contributions, the absence of agreement between the potential contributors may have no significant impact on the costs incurred by the &#x201c;successful&#x201d; offeror &#x2014; because of the outstanding contest in relation to the plaintiff&#x2019;s claim: see <ci:cite searchtype="CASE-REF"><ci:case><ci:caseref ID="cr010670" spanref="cr010670-001"><ci:reporter value="VR"/><ci:edition><ci:date year="1988"/></ci:edition><ci:page num="867"/></ci:caseref><ci:caseref anaphref="cr010670" spanref="cr010670-002"><ci:pinpoint num="869" targettype="page"/></ci:caseref></ci:case><ci:content><citefragment searchtype="CASE-NAME-REF"><emph typestyle="it">Henderson v Simon Engineering (Aust) Pty Ltd</emph></citefragment><citefragment searchtype="CASE-CITE-REF"> <ci:span spanid="cr010670-001">[1988] VR 867</ci:span> <ci:span spanid="cr010670-002">at 869</ci:span></citefragment> <remotelink dpsi="0018" refpt="26891" remotekey1="REFPTID" service="DOC-ID"><inlineobject alttext="Click for CaseBase entry" attachment="web-server" filename="cbcc.gif" type="image"/></remotelink></ci:content></ci:cite>. Alternatively, where an offer is made to several offerees, different costs orders may be made between them, depending on their respective responsibility for the non-acceptance of the offer: <ci:cite searchtype="CASE-REF"><ci:case><ci:caseref ID="cr010671" spanref="cr010671-001"><ci:reporter value="urj"/><ci:refnum num="BC200003515"/></ci:caseref></ci:case><ci:content><citefragment searchtype="CASE-NAME-REF"><emph typestyle="it">Lend Lease Retail Products Pty Ltd v Construction Engineering (Aust) Pty Ltd</emph></citefragment><citefragment searchtype="CASE-CITE-REF"> [2000] VSCA 114; <ci:span spanid="cr010671-001"> BC200003515</ci:span></citefragment> <remotelink dpsi="0018" refpt="313459" remotekey1="REFPTID" service="DOC-ID"><inlineobject alttext="Click for CaseBase entry" attachment="web-server" filename="cbcc.gif" type="image"/></remotelink></ci:content></ci:cite>.</text></p>
</bodytext>
</level><level id="UCPN_UCPR.SGM_UCPN.UCPR.42-18-10" leveltype="para0" subdoc="true" toc-caption="[42.18.10] Land and Environment Court">
